[{"location":"anotherPage.html#The-MyAwesomePackage-Module","page":"An other page","title":"The MyAwesomePackage Module","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#Module-Index","page":"An other page","title":"Module Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"anotherPage.html","page":"An other page","title":"An other page","text":"Modules = [riskMeasures]\nOrder   = [:constant, :type, :function, :macro]","category":"page"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#Detailed-API","page":"An other page","title":"Detailed API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"anotherPage.html","page":"An other page","title":"An other page","text":"Modules = [riskMeasures]\nOrder   = [:constant, :type, :function, :macro]","category":"page"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.CTE2-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.CTE2","text":"An implementation of the Conditional Tail-Value-at-Risk at level α for  a given discrete distribution specified by\n\nstates prob\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.EVaR-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.EVaR","text":"Solving the optimization problem associated with evaluating EVaR as well \tas providing the dual variables\n\nmin (β+log Ee^(t*Y)\t)/t  for t>0\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.EVaR2-Tuple{Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.EVaR2","text":"Solving the optimization problem associated with evaluating EVaR as well \tas providing the dual variables\n\nmin (β+log Ee^(t*Y)\t)/t  for t>0\n\nHere with goldenSearch Algorithm\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.Expectation-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.Expectation","text":"Expectation(states,prob)\n\nCompute the expectation for the random variable given by states under the probability measure given by prob.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.GenCoherent-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.GenCoherent","text":"Coherent risk measure     Calculates a general coherent risk measure based on duality representations\n\nfor coherent risk measures the conditions E(Z) = 1 and Z ≥ 0 are enforced.\nconds needs to be a real valued function F such that F(Z) ≤ 0.\nTo obtain a coherent risk measure F should be positively homegeneous.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.GenConvex-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.GenConvex","text":"Convex risk measure     Calculates a general convex risk measure based on duality representations\n\nconds must specify the feasible set of the convex conjugate\nconjugate must be given via a \"simple\" expression\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.VaR-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.VaR","text":"An implementation of the Value-at-Risk at level α for  a given discrete distribution specified by\n\nstates prob\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.distortion-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.distortion","text":"Distortion risk measure     Calculates the distortion risk measure by numerically integrating the distorted     distribution function for a given distortion function. \n\nThe distribution function is the one for the discrete distribution\nimplied by states and prob vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.entropic-Tuple{Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.entropic","text":"Entropic risk measure  \tas providing the dual variables\n\nt* log Ee^(Y/t)  for t>0\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.mSD-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.mSD","text":"An implementation of the Mean semi-deviation risk measure of \torder p. This is a coherent risk measure which can be nested by \tadjusting the risk level β → β⋅√(Δt)\n\nmSD_β^p(Y) = EY + β ⋅ ||(Y-EY)_+||_p\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.meanDeviation-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.meanDeviation","text":"Mean Deviation risk Measure of order p\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.meanSemiDevi-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.meanSemiDevi","text":"Mean-upper-semideviation of order p from a target\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.meanSemiVariance-Tuple{Float64, Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.meanSemiVariance","text":"Mean-upper-semivariance from a target\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.meanVariance-Tuple{Float64, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.meanVariance","text":"Mean Variance risk Measure\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"anotherPage.html#riskMeasures.spectral-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"An other page","title":"riskMeasures.spectral","text":"Spectral risk measure     Calculates spectral risk measure by numerically integrating product     of quantile function and given spectral function. \n\nThe quantile function is the quantile function for the discrete distribution\nimplied by states and prob vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"index.html#riskMeasures.jl","page":"Index","title":"riskMeasures.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"Documentation for riskMeasures.jl","category":"page"}]
